Detailed Description

cvmx_mio_tws::_sw_twsi

This register allows software to: * Initiate master-mode operations with a write operation, and read the result with a read operation. * Load four bytes for later retrieval (slave mode) with a write operation and check validity with a read operation. * Launch a configuration read/write operation with a write operation and read the result with a read operation.

This register should be read or written by software, and read by the TWSI device. The TWSI device can use either two-byte or five-byte read operations to reference this register. The TWSI device considers this register valid when [V] = 1 and [SLONLY] = 1.
